38Address AccessorInfo::getter(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate) const {
39 Address result = maybe_redirected_getter(isolate);
40 if (!USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL) return result;
41 if (result == kNullAddress) return kNullAddress;
42 return ExternalReference::UnwrapRedirection(result);
43}
44
45void AccessorInfo::init_getter(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate,
46 Address initial_value) {
47 init_maybe_redirected_getter(isolate, initial_value);
48 if (USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL) {
49 init_getter_redirection(isolate);
50 }
51}
52
53void AccessorInfo::set_getter(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate, Address value) {
54 set_maybe_redirected_getter(isolate, value);
55 if (USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL) {
56 init_getter_redirection(isolate);
57 }
58}
59
60void AccessorInfo::init_getter_redirection(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate) {
61 CHECK(USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL);
62 Address value = maybe_redirected_getter(isolate);
63 if (value == kNullAddress) return;
64 value =
65 ExternalReference::Redirect(value, ExternalReference::DIRECT_GETTER_CALL);
66 set_maybe_redirected_getter(isolate, value);
67}
68
69void AccessorInfo::remove_getter_redirection(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate) {
70 CHECK(USE_SIMULATOR_BOOL);
71 Address value = getter(isolate);
72 set_maybe_redirected_getter(isolate, value);
73}
74
75bool AccessorInfo::has_getter(Isolate* isolate) {
76 return maybe_redirected_getter(isolate) != kNullAddress;
77}
78
79bool AccessorInfo::has_setter(Isolate* isolate) {
80 return setter(isolate) != kNullAddress;
81}

91SideEffectType AccessorInfo::setter_side_effect_type() const {
92 return SetterSideEffectTypeBits::decode(flags());
93}
94
95void AccessorInfo::set_setter_side_effect_type(SideEffectType value) {
96 // We do not support describing setters as having no side effect, since
97 // calling set accessors must go through a store bytecode. Store bytecodes
98 // support checking receivers for temporary objects, but still expect
99 // the receiver to be written to.
100 CHECK_NE(value, SideEffectType::kHasNoSideEffect);
101 set_flags(SetterSideEffectTypeBits::update(flags(), value));
102}

104BIT_FIELD_ACCESSORS(AccessorInfo, flags, initial_property_attributes,
105 AccessorInfo::InitialAttributesBits)
106
107void AccessorInfo::clear_padding() {
108 if (FIELD_SIZE(kOptionalPaddingOffset) == 0) return;
109 memset(reinterpret_cast<void*>(address() + kOptionalPaddingOffset), 0,
110 FIELD_SIZE(kOptionalPaddingOffset));
111}
